gnutls_x509_ext_import_basic_constraints(3)                                                       gnutls                                                       gnutls_x509_ext_import_basic_constraints(3)

NAME
       gnutls_x509_ext_import_basic_constraints - API function

SYNOPSIS
       #include <gnutls/x509-ext.h>

       int gnutls_x509_ext_import_basic_constraints(const gnutls_datum_t * ext, unsigned int * ca, int * pathlen);

ARGUMENTS
       const gnutls_datum_t * ext
                   the DER encoded extension data

       unsigned int * ca
                   will be non zero if the CA status is true

       int * pathlen
                   the path length constraint; will be set to -1 for no limit

DESCRIPTION
       This function will return the CA status and path length constraint as written in the PKIX extension 2.5.29.19.

RETURNS
       On success, GNUTLS_E_SUCCESS (0) is returned, otherwise a negative error value.

SINCE
       3.3.0

